## Problem

Current dashboard panels use `position: absolute` / fixed coordinates, so they collide on desktop and completely overlap content on mobile (Playwright mobile screenshot at 390×844 shows the dark sidebar covering the main page).

## Fix

Establish one page-level CSS Grid container in `css/layout.css`:

```css
.app-shell {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header"
    "nav    main"
    "footer footer";
  grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  min-height: 100dvh;
  max-width: 1440px;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

@media (max-width: 1023px) { /* tablet: collapse nav */ }
@media (max-width: 639px)  { /* mobile: single column + bottom nav with safe-area-inset */ }
```

Rules:

- No `position: absolute` on any panel container. Modals use `<dialog>` with backdrop (native or polyfill).
- Touch targets ≥ 44×44 px on all interactive elements.
- Bottom nav on mobile reserves `padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`.

## Scope

1. Add `css/layout.css` with the shell grid.
2. Refactor each HTML file to use the `.app-shell` container.
3. Remove all `position: absolute; top: ...; left: ...;` from panels. Move transient overlays to `<dialog>`.
4. Add responsive breakpoints per plan.md §8e.

## Verification

- Playwright screenshot at 390×844 shows no overlapping content on any dashboard page.
- Playwright screenshot at 1440×900 shows header, nav, and main in clean grid positions.
- `grep -rE "position: *absolute" dashboard/css/` returns only intentional uses (tooltips, dialog backdrops) — zero on layout containers.

Traceability: plan.md §8e "Layout", §8f item 6.

## Problem
`internal/notify/service.go` declares a local variable named `color` which shadows the `image/color` package import:
- Line 652: `color := color.RGBA{...}` — the variable name shadows the package
- Lines 654, 656: subsequent `color.RGBA{}` references fail because `color` is now a variable, not a package

## Fix
Rename the local variable to avoid shadowing. Change lines 652, 654, 656, 670 in `internal/notify/service.go`:
```go
// Line 652: was
color := color.RGBA{100, 181, 246, 255}
// Change to:
clr := color.RGBA{100, 181, 246, 255}

// Lines 654, 656 similarly use clr instead of color
// Line 670: same pattern
```
Also update any uses of the `color` variable further in the same scope to use `clr`.

